== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Taken from ''Haskell Curry'', the name of a famous computer scientist.

=== Noun ===
'''currying'''

# {{computer}} The technique of transforming a function that takes multiple arguments into a function that takes a single argument (the first of the arguments to the original function) and returns a new function that takes the remainder of the arguments and returns the result.

=== Verb ===

''conjugated from [[curry]]''